WEBVTT

00:06.467 --> 00:09.334
>> narrator: IN NEWYORK CITY'S
WAR ON CRIME,

00:09.334 --> 00:11.133
THE WORST CRIMINAL OFFENDERS

00:11.133 --> 00:14.267
ARE PURSUED BY THE DETECTIVES
OF THE MAJOR CASE SQUAD.

00:14.267 --> 00:16.367
THESE ARE THEIR STORIES.

00:18.434 --> 00:19.701
>> SO YOU'RE AUNT WANTS
TO SEE THE BABY.

00:19.701 --> 00:21.133
I DON'T SEE WHY
THAT'S A PROBLEM.

00:21.133 --> 00:23.534
>> BECAUSE IT'S THE LAST
THING I WANNA DO, THAT'S WHY.

00:23.534 --> 00:26.133
>> SO JUST CALL HER
AND TELL HER YOU CAN'T MAKE IT.

00:26.133 --> 00:27.467
SHE'LL UNDERSTAND.

00:27.467 --> 00:31.000
>> SOMETIMES I'D LIKE TO LIVE
ON YOUR PLANET.

00:33.133 --> 00:34.801
HEY, I'M SORRY.

00:34.801 --> 00:36.901
YOU KNOW HOW CRAZY
MY AUNT MAKES ME.

00:36.901 --> 00:40.300
SHE WANTS WHAT SHE WANTS
WHEN SHE WANTS IT.

00:40.300 --> 00:44.434
>> EMMA'S GONNA MISS YOU.
>> ALL RIGHT, WISH ME LUCK.

00:46.067 --> 00:49.501
>> GOOD LUCK.

00:49.501 --> 00:50.767
>> HEY, LUCY.

00:50.767 --> 00:53.567
>> HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

00:57.767 --> 00:59.634
>> OH--HOLD IT.
[laughs]

00:59.634 --> 01:05.033
AH.
 <i>GRACIAS.</i>

01:05.033 --> 01:06.801
>> HOW'S MY AUNT?
>> SHE'S TIRED.

01:06.801 --> 01:08.868
SHE'S BEEN WITH THE DOCTOR
ALL AFTERNOON.

01:08.868 --> 01:12.067
>> DOCTOR? WHAT'S WRONG?
>> SHE'S NOT WELL.

01:12.067 --> 01:14.067
>> WHAT ABOUT HER MOOD?

01:14.067 --> 01:17.300
>> WHAT YOU'D EXPECT.

01:17.300 --> 01:18.968
>> I EXPECTED TO SEE HER,
ANDRE.

01:18.968 --> 01:20.367
>> THE BABY HAS A COLD.

01:20.367 --> 01:21.834
I DECIDED
IT WAS BEST TO LET HER SLEEP.

01:21.834 --> 01:25.267
>> YOUR HOTEL'S NOT THAT FAR.
I'LL JUST GET MY COAT.

01:25.267 --> 01:28.601
>> NO, NO, YOU CAN'T AFFORD
TO CATCH WHAT SHE HAS.

01:28.601 --> 01:31.000
>> IT'S BEEN SIX MONTHS.

01:31.000 --> 01:34.400
I WANT TO SEE HER TOMORROW.
NO EXCUSES.

